[1mDESCRIPTION[0m
     For the  current window  , sets the mouse-cursor to one of a set of pre-
     defined images.  The GLUT symbolic constant IDs are:

      -  [1mGLUT_CURSOR_RIGHT_ARROW[0m
      -  [1mGLUT_CURSOR_LEFT_ARROW[0m
      -  [1mGLUT_CURSOR_INFO[0m
      -  [1mGLUT_CURSOR_DESTROY[0m
      -  [1mGLUT_CURSOR_HELP[0m
      -  [1mGLUT_CURSOR_CYCLE[0m
      -  [1mGLUT_CURSOR_SPRAY[0m
      -  [1mGLUT_CURSOR_WAIT[0m
      -  [1mGLUT_CURSOR_TEXT[0m
      -  [1mGLUT_CURSOR_CROSSHAIR[0m
      -  [1mGLUT_CURSOR_UP_DOWN[0m
      -  [1mGLUT_CURSOR_LEFT_RIGHT[0m
      -  [1mGLUT_CURSOR_TOP_SIDE[0m
      -  [1mGLUT_CURSOR_BOTTOM_SIDE[0m
      -  [1mGLUT_CURSOR_LEFT_SIDE[0m
      -  [1mGLUT_CURSOR_RIGHT_SIDE[0m
      -  [1mGLUT_CURSOR_TOP_LEFT_CORNER[0m
      -  [1mGLUT_CURSOR_TOP_RIGHT_CORNER[0m
      -  [1mGLUT_CURSOR_BOTTOM_RIGHT_CORNER[0m
      -  [1mGLUT_CURSOR_BOTTOM_LEFT_CORNER[0m

     Additionally, there are the following special cases:

      [1mGLUT_CURSOR_FULL_CROSSHAIR  [22mThis cursor, where supported, draws a
     crosshair the full width and height of the display.  It may be mapped by
     OpenGLUT to the  [1mGLUT_CURSOR_CROSSHAIR,  [22mhowever.

      [1mGLUT_CURSOR_NONE  [22mTurn the mouse cursor invisibile.

      [1mGLUT_CURSOR_INHERIT  [22mTake the cursor that the parent window provides.

[1mCAVEATS[0m
     The X branch of OpenGLUT does not do thorough error checking.

     The X branch of OpenGLUT always converts  [1mFULL_CROSSHAIR  [22mto  [1mCROSSHAIR.[0m
      This is acceptable, but if a host system supports a fullscreen
     crosshair, it would be nice to support that.

     Out of range  [1mcursorID  [22mvalues generate warnings.

     Has no visible effect if the  current window   is of type  [1mGLUT_OFFSCREEN[0m
      .

[1mBUGS[0m
